description: Test suite failures during 'make check' phase, possibly due to environment or test case inconsistencies. Error 1 in test-suite.log reported.
Missing installation candidate for automake_1.11 package required for build process, causing failure in package file list generation.
Incompatible pointer type error in _ULx86_sigreturn call at x86/Gos-linux.c:302 during compilation, treated as fatal error.
Kernel NULL pointer dereference and segmentation faults during test execution (buf-ring-nommap.t, coredump.t), resulting in killed processes (ret 137).
hasher-privd exceeded idle time limit (3600 seconds) during rebuild process, leading to build failure.
Undefined reference to ICU library function 'ucnv_open_76' during linking of zmf2raw executable, indicating missing ICU development dependencies.
Missing dev86 package required for build process, causing failure in package file list generation.
CMake configuration failed: Could NOT find webp components (missing: webp_LIBRARY, webp_INCLUDE_PATH, webpdemux_LIBRARY).
Fatal sign comparison error (-Werror=sign-compare) in pam_lastlog.c:572 between __uint32_t and time_t types, treating warnings as errors.
Conflicting type declaration for fpos_t (long vs standard library's definition) in std.h:95 during compilation of sgmlsasp.c and getopt.c.
